# Agent skills awareness

Before planning, stories, design, architecture, coding, testing, or reviewing — check `.cursor/skills/` for a matching skill. Read the relevant `SKILL.md` before acting.

## Skill router

| Task | Skill | Folder |
|------|-------|--------|
| 2+ stories at once, batch / wave / tranche, parallel agents | `parallel-story-orchestrator` | `parallel-story-orchestrator/` |
| User stories, backlog, INVEST, sprint planning | `user-story-generator` | `user-story-generator-cursor/` |
| Product / UX / design direction | `jony-ive-product-design` | `jony-ive-product-design/` |
| TDD, failing tests first, red/green/refactor | `tdd-workflow` | `tdd-workflow/` |
| Security review before story done | `code-vulnerability-analysis` | `code-vulnerability-analysis/` |
| Architecture, ADRs, system design | `architecture-designer` | `architecture-designer/` |
| OpenSpec change lifecycle | `openspec-*` | matching folder |
| Story-done checklist | `gt-story-done` | `gt-story-done/` |
| Agent memory read/write | `memory-protocol` | `memory-protocol/` |
| Repo bootstrap | `gt-project-bootstrap` | `gt-project-bootstrap/` |

**Mandatory:** user-story creation → `user-story-generator`. Product/UX design → `jony-ive-product-design`. Story implementation → `tdd-workflow`. **2+ stories run concurrently → `parallel-story-orchestrator` (single agent must not implement multiple stories itself).** Before done → `code-vulnerability-analysis` (or quick Cursor review-security if scope is tiny — note which in work item comment).

## Deliverable paths

Resolve output directories from `project-config.yaml`:

- Backlog: `planning.backlog_dir` (default `docs/backlog/`)
- Security: `planning.security_output_dir` (default `docs/security/`)

## When no skill applies

Say so briefly in work notes and follow repo rules. Cite skill results in planning-system comments when used.

Pairs with: `delivery-methodology`, `story-and-tdd-first`, `persona-routing`.
